<section class="ws-reviews ls-reviews center learning-testimonials">
  <div class="swiper ls-reviews__slider">
    <div class="swiper-wrapper ws-reviews__cards ls-reviews__cards">
      <div class="swiper-slide">
        <p class="body-paragraph ws-reviews__cards--review">"I had the pleasure of working with Deo over the course of several years. He first sought to understand the needs of our school community by reaching out to key stakeholders including Board members, parents, students, school administrators, and staff members. Deo and his team accomplished this through individual and group in-person meetings as well as through multiple surveys that we developed together. After analysis of the information from the conversations and surveys, Deo presented the findings back to the stakeholder groups to make sure what was summarized truly represented their thoughts. Throughout the process, Deo was helpful and came from a place of providing opportunities for everyone not only to be heard but to be understood. We then partnered together with our school leadership team members to use the information gleaned to create meaningful, strategic, actionable goals for the School District's Three-Year Strategic Plan. Deo assisted me with determining the need for a District Director of Equity, Curriculum, Instruction, and Assessment position which we now have in place. I invited Deo to attend our annual school administrator leadership team Fall Momentum Meeting and he did a fabulous job of summarizing the steps we had taken and getting everyone excited about the direction we are heading to support all staff members, students, and families in the District. I am grateful for Deo's thoughtful approach while also holding everyone accountable and providing suggestions for ways we can continue improving the educational experience for all involved. Thank you, Deo!"</p>
        <button type="button" class="button-unstyled ws-reviews__cards--read-more">read more</button>
        <p class="ws-reviews__cards--meta body-paragraph">
          <strong>Dr. Joanne Roberts</strong>
          <br>
          <span>Superintendent of the Lebanon School District, Lebanon, New Hampshire</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="swiper-slide">
        <p class="body-paragraph ws-reviews__cards--review">"Deo Mwano has a magic of goodness. I think it comes from having such a powerful and generous heart. His energy inspires. The vitality that he brings to students, and what he gave to me as a colleague, generates tremendous goodwill and insight. He summons up and frees the creative spirit. That kind of innovation and connection is rare. Deo is himself a special source of light and a talented guide."</p>
        <button type="button" class="button-unstyled ws-reviews__cards--read-more">read more</button>
        <p class="ws-reviews__cards--meta body-paragraph">
          <strong>RG Richards</strong>
          <br>
          <span>Phillips Exeter Academy Chair, Theatre Instructor</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="swiper-slide">
        <p class="body-paragraph ws-reviews__cards--review">"Deo brought an informative, high energy, and inspirational workshop to students during a critical time. We asked for an opportunity for students to learn more, reflect on their own experiences, and identify what they can do to positively impact the culture in their school. Deo did a great job and really engaged students."</p>
        <button type="button" class="button-unstyled ws-reviews__cards--read-more">read more</button>
        <p class="ws-reviews__cards--meta body-paragraph">
          <strong>Michele Holt-Shannon</strong>
          <br>
          <span>Director of New Hampshire Listens, University of New Hampshire Carsey Center</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="swiper-slide">
        <p class="body-paragraph ws-reviews__cards--review">"Deo worked with NH HOBY to facilitate a piece of our program where we work to introduce the topic of privilege to high-school sophomores, young leaders from the state of NH. After many years of not feeling like we hit the point home, we were so happy that Deo did this year. His energy, story and ability to engage was unparalleled to any of our internal resources and we were so glad to have brought him in to speak at our seminar."</p>
        <button type="button" class="button-unstyled ws-reviews__cards--read-more">read more</button>
        <p class="ws-reviews__cards--meta body-paragraph">
          <strong>Kate Aiken</strong>
          <br>
          <span>Former Director of Program of HOBY NH</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="swiper-slide">
        <p class="body-paragraph ws-reviews__cards--review">"Having Deo (Shaq & Martin, too) at NMH School was an amazing experience for our students and faculty. We appreciated hearing his personal story in the keynote address, as Deo raised important questions about identity, belonging, and living well in community together. Most impressive was his music & dance workshop with about 60 students; he was fired up; Deo was fired up, got them fired up, and a number of kids commented that it was the best workshop they had ever attended. Simply put, it was an awesome afternoon and we are thrilled Deo was able to share his talents with NMH School."</p>
        <button type="button" class="button-unstyled ws-reviews__cards--read-more">read more</button>
